    "body": "As a user I want to have microarchitecture specific flags injected for Intel compilers so that I would compile by default code that is optimized for the target of the installation.\r\n\r\n### Rationale\r\n\r\nWe already support this feature for GCC since #3206 and need to extend the capability to other compilers as well\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nWhat needs to be done is carefully reviewing docs and man pages, and encode in [this file](https://github.com/spack/spack/blob/develop/lib/spack/llnl/util/cpu/microarchitectures.json) the information found.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\nA non exhaustive list of pages we might want to consult:\r\n\r\n- [Intel C++ compiler Reference](https://software.intel.com/en-us/cpp-compiler-developer-guide-and-reference)\r\n- [Intel Fortran compiler Reference](https://software.intel.com/en-us/fortran-compiler-developer-guide-and-reference)\r\n- auto-dispatch PR #11697",
